{"word":"ἱδρυτέος","slug":"ἱδρυτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἱδρυτέος</b></el> <el>(ἱδρῡτέος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:ἱδρύω'><el>ἱδρύω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>one must inaugurate</i> a statue, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, <el>ἱδρυτέον</el> <i>one must sit idle</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}